{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.hasPushouts_of_hasBinaryCoproducts_of_hasCoequalizers\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Limits</span>.<span class=\"name\">hasPushouts_of_hasBinaryCoproducts_of_hasCoequalizers</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v, u}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/BinaryProducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasBinaryCoproducts\">HasBinaryCoproducts</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Equalizers.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasCoequalizers\">HasCoequalizers</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Pullback/HasPullback.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasPushouts\">HasPushouts</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If a category has all binary coproducts and all coequalizers, then it also has all pushouts.\nAs usual, this is not an instance, since there may be a more direct way to construct pushouts. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.hasPushouts_of_hasBinaryCoproducts_of_hasCoequalizers","kind":"theorem","line":93,"name":"CategoryTheory.Limits.hasPushouts_of_hasBinaryCoproducts_of_hasCoequalizers","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.lean#L93-L97"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.hasColimit_span_of_hasColimit_pair_of_hasColimit_parallelPair\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Limits</span>.<span class=\"name\">hasColimit_span_of_hasColimit_pair_of_hasColimit_parallelPair</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">𝒞</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v, u}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X </span><span class=\"fn\">Y </span><span class=\"fn\">Z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">X</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">Y</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> : <span class=\"fn\">X</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">Z</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/HasLimits.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasColimit\">HasColimit</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/BinaryProducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.pair\">pair</a> <span class=\"fn\">Y</span> <span class=\"fn\">Z</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/HasLimits.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasColimit\">HasColimit</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Equalizers.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.parallelPair\">parallelPair</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.comp\">CategoryStruct.comp</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/BinaryProducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.coprod.inl\">coprod.inl</a>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.comp\">CategoryStruct.comp</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/BinaryProducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.coprod.inr\">coprod.inr</a>)</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/HasLimits.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasColimit\">HasColimit</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Pullback/Cospan.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.span\">span</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If the coproduct `Y ⨿ Z` and the coequalizer of `f ≫ ι₁` and `g ≫ ι₂` exist, then the\npushout of `f` and `g` exists: It is given by composing the inclusions with the coequalizer. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.hasColimit_span_of_hasColimit_pair_of_hasColimit_parallelPair","kind":"theorem","line":66,"name":"CategoryTheory.Limits.hasColimit_span_of_hasColimit_pair_of_hasColimit_parallelPair","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.lean#L66-L87"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.hasPullbacks_of_hasBinaryProducts_of_hasEqualizers\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Limits</span>.<span class=\"name\">hasPullbacks_of_hasBinaryProducts_of_hasEqualizers</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v, u}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/BinaryProducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasBinaryProducts\">HasBinaryProducts</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Equalizers.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasEqualizers\">HasEqualizers</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Pullback/HasPullback.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasPullbacks\">HasPullbacks</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If a category has all binary products and all equalizers, then it also has all pullbacks.\nAs usual, this is not an instance, since there may be a more direct way to construct\npullbacks. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.hasPullbacks_of_hasBinaryProducts_of_hasEqualizers","kind":"theorem","line":56,"name":"CategoryTheory.Limits.hasPullbacks_of_hasBinaryProducts_of_hasEqualizers","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.lean#L56-L61"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.hasLimit_cospan_of_hasLimit_pair_of_hasLimit_parallelPair\"><span class=\"name\">CategoryTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">Limits</span>.<span class=\"name\">hasLimit_cospan_of_hasLimit_pair_of_hasLimit_parallelPair</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">𝒞</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Category\">Category.{v, u}</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X </span><span class=\"fn\">Y </span><span class=\"fn\">Z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">C</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">X</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">Z</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Y</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Quiver/Basic.html#Quiver.Hom\">⟶</a> <span class=\"fn\">Z</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/HasLimits.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasLimit\">HasLimit</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/BinaryProducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.pair\">pair</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span> <span class=\"fn\">Y</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/HasLimits.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasLimit\">HasLimit</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Equalizers.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.parallelPair\">parallelPair</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.comp\">CategoryStruct.comp</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/BinaryProducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.prod.fst\">prod.fst</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.comp\">CategoryStruct.comp</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/BinaryProducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.prod.snd\">prod.snd</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/HasLimits.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.HasLimit\">HasLimit</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Pullback/Cospan.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.cospan\">cospan</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If the product `X ⨯ Y` and the equalizer of `π₁ ≫ f` and `π₂ ≫ g` exist, then the\npullback of `f` and `g` exists: It is given by composing the equalizer with the projections. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.hasLimit_cospan_of_hasLimit_pair_of_hasLimit_parallelPair","kind":"theorem","line":29,"name":"CategoryTheory.Limits.hasLimit_cospan_of_hasLimit_pair_of_hasLimit_parallelPair","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Constructions/Pullbacks.lean#L29-L50"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Shapes.BinaryProducts","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Shapes.Equalizers","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Shapes.Pullback.HasPullback"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Constructions.Pullbacks"}